AUDIO: 'All right, YouTube. What is good? It\'s your boy Rebel back with another video. And today we are going to be taking a look at BooBoo image edit. Now, if you haven\'t watched my latest video on BooBoo image base and turbo, go check that out because I talk about the models'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'architecture and how it works. However, we are going to skip over all of the technical aspects of the model today and we are going to jump into installation. So, on the main repo page, there is only'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one quantization available and that is my guffs here. So, I will have this linked in the description. Now, if you watched my last video for the base and turbo, you already have the FP8 encoder'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and the flux one VAE, but if you don\'t, you can click these underlined comfy org links and it will bring you to the necessary files to download them if you don\'t have them. Also, in the main repo'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for BooBoo image from the comfy org team, there is a Lora\'s folder. Now, in this Lora\'s folder, there is a turbo Lora. So, this was pulled from the main turbo model, the distilled model, and'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what this does is it allows you to open up the base and edit model to more variability based on step count and CFG. This allows you to essentially utilize partial or full distillation with both'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of the models. So, that is also an option for you to download, but in my repo, after you choose your guff of choice, you can download the workflow here and then you can throw it into'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'comfy and it will look something like this. Now, starting on the left here, we have four load image nodes with four image scale down nodes. Now, these image scale nodes just lower the resolution of'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your image automatically by keeping the resolution scale correct. So, essentially these 2048 by 2048 images will scale down to 1024 by 1024. And'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'underneath the load image one node, you have a get image size node. All this does is it passes the dimensions of your first image to the empty latent so that'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you don\'t have to manually adjust your width and height. You can just have it take the original resolution of the first image. Moving over, we have either a load diffusion model or a unit loader node hosting our edit model. We have a'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'load VAE node hosting our flux one VAE. We have our load clip node hosting our Qwen 3VL 8B FP8 scaled encoder. We have our empty latent image node. And then we'

[02:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have our model sampling. And then we have a load LoRA node hosting the turbo LoRA. Now, the turbo LoRA can be played around with values. I do recommend, however, 0.5 if you are going to do'

[02:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'anything. And then you\'re going to want to drop your step count down to about eight or 10 with a CFG of anywhere from 3.5 to 5.0. And then we have our K sampler. Now, if you do not run the'

[02:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'turbo LoRA, you are going to want to run about 20 steps with a CFG of 3.5. And you can play around with this value and get it anywhere from 3.5 to 5. It\'s just going to be dependent on what references'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'re using and your prompt and what you actually want in your generation. And then here we\'re just running the simple VAE decode node. Now, with the workflow accounted for, I do have some examples for you guys today and we will'

[03:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'be taking a look at those. So, for our first example, we have the usual cover photo of the person holding the sign reading booboo image edit guffs. Pretty standard image. Now, for reference, you can see the original image on the left.'

[03:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'There is very minimal quality loss between the reference image and the generation. I was actually very surprised when I saw this first edit. Here we have a style transfer to anime.'

